:: Avery Valentines Invite Street End
<<effects>>

<<if $avery_valentines.invite>>
	<<if $phase is 1>>
		"Good." Avery looks pleased. "Most have to wait a year to book a table, and it's rare for anyone to get a reservation like this at such short notice." <<His>> voice lowers as <<he>> continues,
		<<if C.npc.Avery.rage gte 40 and $averyragerevealed gte 1>>
			"I expect you to show the proper amount of gratitude at the end of all this,
		<<else>>
			"I hope you appreciate all my hard work,
		<</if>>
		<<pcpetname "Avery">>. I'll see you at our usual time."
		<br><br>
	<<elseif $phase is 2>>
		<<if $avery_mansion>>
			"Good." Avery nods, smoothing <<his>> expression over. "I'll see you in the garage at our usual time."
			<br><br>
		<<else>>
			"Good." Avery nods, smoothing <<his>> expression over. "I'll see you on Domus Street at our usual time."
			<br><br>
		<</if>>
	<</if>>
	With that, <<he>> rolls up <<his>> window and drives off.
	<br><br>
	<<if $avery_mansion>>
		<i>Avery will expect you to meet <<him>> in the garage at <<ampm 21 00>> February 14th.</i>
		<br><br>
	<<else>>
		<i>Avery will expect you to meet <<him>> on Domus Street at <<ampm 20 00>> on February 14th.</i>
		<br><br>
	<</if>>
<<else>>
	<<if $averyragerevealed gte 1>>
		Avery's frown turns into a scowl. "Fine," <<he>> grits out. "Have it your way. We'll see if I ever make such an offer again." With that, <<he>> rolls up <<his>> window and drives off.
	<<else>>
		Avery's brows furrow, and <<he>> sighs. "Very well, then. If you insist." It looks like <<he>> wants to say something else, but <<he>> just shakes <<his>> head, rolls up <<his>> window, and drives off.
	<</if>><<npcincr Avery rage 1>><<garage>>
	<br><br>
<</if>>

<<endevent>>
