<</if>>

:: Avery Valentines 2
<<effects>><<set $outside to 0>>

<<pass 5>><<npc Avery 1>><<generatep2>><<generatep3>><<person1>>

Avery opens the door for you, and shuts it once you've climbed in. On the drive, <<he>> talks about how prestigious this restaurant is, listing off names of the famous and powerful that have visited.
<br><br>
You soon arrive, and Avery comes to a slow stop. A valet takes Avery's keys as you exit, and Avery takes your arm, leading you towards the entrance.<<if $fame.model gte 400>> You turn a few heads as you walk.<</if>>
<br><br>
There's a short queue, comprised of couples. A <<person2>><<person>> in front of you leans down to kiss <<his>> partner's cheek. The partner, a <<person3>><<person>>, <<laughs>> and looks away.
<br><br>
Meanwhile, at your side, Avery scrolls through <<person1>><<his>> phone to find your reservation code.
<br><br>
<<link [[Next|Avery Valentines 3]]>><</link>>
<br>

:: Avery Valentines 3
<<effects>>

When you reach the doors, the doorman asks for Avery's name, and scans the code on <<his>> phone, before ushering you both inside.
<br><br>
The restaurant is lavish, the furniture ornate. A band plays mellow orchestral music, and the chandeliers cast a golden glow throughout. Everyone here, including the servers, are dressed in expensive and fashionable attire. Avery looks like <<he>> belongs,
<<if $fame.social gte 800>>
	and <span class="green">so do you</span>.
<<elseif $speech_attitude is "bratty" and !$speech_attitude_avery>>
	but you don't bother trying to match <<him>>.
<<else>>
	and you try your best to comport yourself in appropriate fashion.
<</if>>
<br><br>
Avery's coat is passed off, and then the host of the restaurant leads you to your table. It's a small and intimate table for two, with placards bearing Avery's name and your own. They're taken away by the host, who hands out menus, and informs you that your server will arrive soon.
<br><br>
You and Avery are left alone.
<br><br>
<<link [[Thank Avery for taking you out|Avery Valentines 4]]>><<set $phase to 0>><<set $avery_valentines.talk to "thank">><</link>>
<br>
<<if !$avery_valentines.reservations>>
	<<link [[Ask how Avery got dinner reservations on such short notice|Avery Valentines 4]]>><<set $phase to 0>><<set $avery_valentines.talk to "reservations">><</link>>
	<br>
<</if>>
<<link [[Just look at the menu|Avery Valentines 5]]>><<set $phase to 1>><</link>>
<br>

:: Avery Valentines 4
<<effects>>

<<switch $avery_valentines.talk>>
<<case "thank">>
	<<set $averySeen.pushUnique("vday_thank")>>
<<if $speech_attitude is "meek" or $speech_attitude_avery>>
	"Thank you for inviting me, Avery," you say.
<<elseif $speech_attitude is "bratty">>
	"Thanks for taking me here. This place is pretty swanky."
<<else>>
	"Thanks for inviting me, Avery," you say. "I've never been to a place like this before."
<</if>>
<br><br>
Avery looks up from scanning <<his>> menu and smiles. "Of course. Anything for my <<= $player.gender_appearance is "m" ? "prince" : "princess">>."
<br><br>
<<case "reservations">>
	<<set $averySeen.pushUnique("vday_reservations")>>
	<<if $speech_attitude is "meek" or $speech_attitude_avery>>
		"Um, Avery? I've been curious. How did you get these reservations on such short notice?" you ask. "I heard you have to wait a year to get a table."
	<<elseif $speech_attitude is "bratty">>
		"Hey, how did you get those reservations in only two weeks?" you ask. "You have to wait a year for this place."
	<<else>>
		"How did you get those reservations on such short notice?" you ask. "Don't you have to wait a year to get a table at this place?"
	<</if>>
	<br>
	Avery dons a
	<<if $avery_fate is "ascended">>
		smug smile. "For others, that's true." <<He>> lifts <<his>> menu. "But queues don't apply to me. You'd do well to remember that."
		<br>
		<<= $averyragerevealed is 1 and C.npc.Avery.rage gte 60 ? "There's a slight threat in <<his>> tone." : "<<He>> gives you a flash of a smile before looking back down at <<his>> menu.">>
	<<else>>
		mysterious smile. "Ah, well. It's useful knowing the right kind of people." <<He>> looks back down at <<his>> menu. "But I'd prefer you focus on enjoying the experience, rather than how it came to be."
	<</if>>
	<br><br>
<<case "vday_date">>
	<<set $averySeen.pushUnique("vday_date")>>
	<<if $speech_attitude is "meek" or $speech_attitude_avery>>
		"Have you brought anyone else here before?"
	<<elseif $speech_attitude is "bratty">>
		"So, brought anyone here besides me, or am I special?"
	<<else>>
		"Have you ever brought anyone else here?"
	<</if>>
	<br>
	"No, I haven't, actually," Avery says, amused. "No one but you. Surprised?"
	<br><br>
<<case "past_lovers">>
	<<set $averySeen.pushUnique("past_lovers")>>
	<<if $speech_attitude is "meek" or $speech_attitude_avery>>Keeping your voice gentle and low, you ask<<else>>You ask<</if>> about Avery's past relationships. You can't be the only one.
	<br>
	"Could it be that you're jealous, my <<pcpetname "Avery" "my">>?" Avery asks, rather than answering your question. <<He>> seems pleased by the idea.<<npcincr Avery love 1>><<glove>>
	<br>
	"I've been in relationships before, of course. But most people my age have. If you're concerned I'm seeing anyone other than you, then worry not." <<He>> flashes you a <<= $averyragerevealed is 1 ? "smirk" : "smile">>. "You're the only one."
	<br><br>
<<case "first_meeting">>
	<<set $averySeen.pushUnique("first_meeting")>>
	You ask Avery about the day you met, and why <<he>> approached you.
	<br>
	Avery's brows rise in idle surprise. <<He>> considers a moment, then <<laughs>>. "In all honesty? I saw you and thought, 'What a cute <<girl>>.'
	<<if $averySeen.includes("meetParkPolice") or !$averySeen.includes("meetPark")>>
		A cute <<girl>> being harassed by a <<= $averySeen.includes("meetParkPolice") ? "police officer" : "random stranger">> at that. I just had to step in."
	<<else>>
		A cute <<girl>> in need of help climbing that statue. I just had to step in."
	<</if>>
	<br><br>
<<case "first_meeting_thank">>
	<<set $averySeen.pushUnique("first_meeting_thank")>>
	<<if $averyromance>>
		<<if $speech_attitude is "meek" or $speech_attitude_avery>>
			"Y-you saved me when we first met." You feel your face heating, and you smile at <<him>>. "Thank you, Avery."
		<<elseif $speech_attitude is "bratty">>
			"You did save me back when we first met." You look away for a moment, face warming. "Thanks, I guess."
		<<else>>
			"You saved me when we first met." You smile at <<him>>. "Thank you, Avery."
		<</if>>
		<br><br>
		"Of course." <<He>> gives you a wink. "Any time."
	<<else>>
		<<if $speech_attitude is "meek" or $speech_attitude_avery>>
			"Y-you saved me when we first met." You look down at your hands. "Thank you, Avery."
		<<elseif $speech_attitude is "bratty">>
			"You did save me back when we first met." You snort. "Right. Because I'm cute."
		<<else>>
			"You saved me when we first met. Thank you, Avery."
		<</if>>
		<br><br>
		<<if $speech_attitude is "bratty" and !$speech_attitude_avery>>
			<<He>> lets out an amused hum. "It's true," <<he>> says with a wink.
		<<else>>
			"Of course." <<He>> gives you a wink. "Any time."
		<</if>>
	<</if>>
	<br><br>
<</switch>>

<<if !$averySeen.includes("vday_thank")>>
	<<link [[Thank Avery for taking you out|Avery Valentines 4]]>><<set $avery_valentines.talk to "thank">><</link>>
	<br>
<</if>>
<<if !$avery_valentines.reservations and !$averySeen.includes("vday_reservations")>>
	<<link [[Ask how Avery got dinner reservations on such short notice|Avery Valentines 4]]>><<set $avery_valentines.talk to "reservations">><</link>>
	<br>
<</if>>
<<if !$averySeen.includes("vday_date")>>
	<<link [[Ask if Avery's taken anyone else here before|Avery Valentines 4]]>><<set $avery_valentines.talk to "vday_date">><</link>>
	<br>
<</if>>
<<if $averySeen.includes("vday_date") and !$averySeen.includes("past_lovers")>>
	<<link [[Ask about Avery's past relationships|Avery Valentines 4]]>><<set $avery_valentines.talk to "past_lovers">><</link>>
	<br>
<</if>>
<<if $averySeen.includes("past_lovers") and !$averySeen.includes("first_meeting")>>
	<<link [[Ask why Avery first approached you|Avery Valentines 4]]>><<set $avery_valentines.talk to "first_meeting">><</link>>
	<br>
<</if>>
<<if $averySeen.includes("first_meeting") and !$averySeen.includes("first_meeting_thank")>>
	<<link [[Thank Avery for saving you when you first met|Avery Valentines 4]]>><<set $avery_valentines.talk to "first_meeting_thank">><</link>>
	<br>
<</if>>
