:: Avery Valentines 5
<<effects>>

<<pass 10>>

You<<if $phase is 1>> decide not to say anything, and<</if>> look over your menu. Soon enough, a server arrives with another, detailing available wines. You're informed which dishes go with which wines, then the server slips away, promising to return soon.
<br><br>
Avery hums as <<he>> peruses the new menu. <<He>> glances up to catch your eye, and smiles. "Feel free to order whatever you like, by the way. It's not every day you can visit a restaurant like this."
<br><br>
<<link [[Order something delicious|Avery Valentines 6]]>><<set $avery_valentines.food to "tasty">><</link>>
<br>
<<link [[Order something expensive|Avery Valentines 6]]>><<set $avery_valentines.food to "expensive">><</link>>
<br>
<<link [[Order something you're unfamiliar with|Avery Valentines 6]]>><<set $avery_valentines.food to "new">><</link>>
<br>

:: Avery Valentines 6
<<effects>>

<<pass 10>>

<<if $avery_valentines.food is "tasty">>
	You decide to order something you recognise. It's a familiar dish, but you imagine it will be more delicious when made in a restaurant with a reputation like this one.
<<elseif $avery_valentines.food is "expensive">>
	As Avery said, it's not every day you can order food at a place like this. You decide on the most expensive meal on the menu. If Avery is upset about it, <<his>> placid expression gives nothing away.
<<else>>
	As Avery said, it's not every day you can order food at a place like this. You decide to try something you've never had before.
<</if>>
<br><br>
The server comes by again, and both of you give your orders. Avery orders a bottle of wine to go with them as well. The menus are whisked away, and once again the two of you are left alone.
<br><br>
Avery opens <<his>> mouth to speak, but pauses when <<he>> notices the building argument of a couple at a nearby table.
<br><br>
<<link [[Next|Avery Valentines 7]]>><</link>>
<br>

:: Avery Valentines 7
<<effects>>

It's the <<person2>><<person>> and <<person3>><<person>> you saw outside. Far from bashful now, the <<person>> is glaring daggers at <<his>> partner, who is scowling back in return. It's a jarring departure from how they appeared earlier.
<br><br>
"I'm so sick of it!" the <<person>> says, now loud enough for you to make out the words. A quick glance around tells you that you two are not the only one hearing <<him>>. People look anywhere but there. "Having a big salary doesn't mean you get to act like a <<if $NPCList[1].pronoun is "f">>queen<<else>>king<</if>>!"
<br><br>
"What are you talking about?" the <<person2>><<person>> retorts, just as heated. "I'm not asking much of you! Just some more work around the house since I'm bringing in more money between the two of us! Is that really too much to ask for?"
<br><br>
Avery looks at the couple askance with a slight frown. The pair's very public argument is ruining the atmosphere of the restaurant, and <<person1>><<hes>> not the only one that seems bothered.
<br><br>
<<link [[Intervene|Avery Valentines Intervene]]>><</link>>
<br>
<<link [[Try to ignore them|Avery Valentines Ignore]]>><</link>>
<br>

:: Avery Valentines Intervene
<<effects>>

<<if $speech_attitude is "meek">>
	"Um, excuse me?" you call out just loud enough to be heard over the argument.
<<elseif $speech_attitude is "bratty">>
	"Hey, 'lovebirds,'" you call out over the arguing couple.
<<else>>
	"Excuse me," you call out to the arguing couple.
<</if>>
<br><br>
They drop silent, and they turn their ire towards you. In your periphery, you notice Avery <<= $averyragerevealed gte 1 ? "gives you a subtle quelling stare" : "stiffens up, and shakes <<his>> head">>.
<br><br>
<<link [[Try to help|Avery Valentines Intervene 2]]>><<set $phase to 0>><</link>><<englishdifficulty 400 600>>
<br>
<<link [[Apologise|Avery Valentines Ignore]]>><<set $phase to 1>><</link>>
<br>

:: Avery Valentines Ignore
<<effects>>

<<if $phase is 1>>
	You apologise, and the couple returns to their fighting. Avery relaxes.
	<br><br>
<</if>>
You, Avery, and everyone else seated nearby do your best to ignore the arguing couple. Each goes on a tirade about how the other doesn't appreciate them, and how they don't feel cared about. <<stress 6>><<gstress>>
<br><br>
A brave member of the staff comes by, and the couple leave the restaurant, fuming.
<br><br>
Avery sighs across from you. "Finally."
<br><br>

<<link [[Agree|Avery Valentines Ignore 2]]>><<set $phase to 1>><</link>>
<br>
<<link [[Express sympathy for the couple|Avery Valentines Ignore 2]]>><<set $phase to 2>><</link>>
<br>
<<link [[Say nothing|Avery Valentines 8]]>><<set $phase to 0>><</link>>
<br>

:: Avery Valentines Ignore 2
<<effects>>

<<if $phase is 1>>
	You nod along. Their argument was ruining the ambience, and it's not every day you get to visit a restaurant like this.
	<br><br>
	<<link [[Next|Avery Valentines 8]]>><</link>>
<<else>>
	<<if $speech_attitude is "meek" or $speech_attitude_avery>>
		"It seems like such a shame." you say. "Breaking up on Valentine's Day, I mean."
	<<elseif $speech_attitude is "bratty">>
		"It's Valentine's Day." You huff. "That's the last holiday you should be breaking up with your partner on."
	<<else>>
		"It seems tragic to be fighting on Valentine's Day of all days."
	<</if>>
	<br><br>
	"Do you think so? Many couples break up on Valentine's Day, you know." <<He>> looks in the direction the couple stormed off in with a <<= $averyragerevealed is 1 ? "dismissive" : "placid">> expression. "The bigger tragedy is wasting their reservation like that. Though making up this time wouldn't have changed anything. They'd be right back at it again the moment they stopped getting what they wanted out of each other. That's all any relationship is, once you've stripped away the trappings: A transaction."
	<br><br>
	<<He>> says the last part as though <<hes>> imparting some great wisdom to you.
	<br><br>

	<<link [[Agree|Avery Valentines Cynic]]>><<set $avery_valentines.opinion to "cynic">><<set $phase to 1>><</link>>
	<br>
	<<link [[Disagree|Avery Valentines Romantic]]>><<set $avery_valentines.opinion to "romantic">><</link>>
