		<<endcombat>>
		<<set $bus to "avery_bedroom">>
		<<avery_mansion_end_links>>
	<</if>>
<<elseif $finish is 1>> /* Asked to stop */
	Avery lets you go, though <<he>>
	<<if $averyragerevealed is 1 and C.npc.Avery.rage gte 60>>
		doesn't look any less angry. "Fine," <<he>> snaps,
	<<else>>
		still seems irate. "Very well then," <<he>> says,
	<</if>>
	pulling away from you.
	<<if $avery_mansion?.schedule is "dinner">>
		"It's time for dinner, anyway." <<He>> stalks off in the direction of the dining room.
	<<elseif _dirty_room>>
		"You have some cleaning to do, anyway." <<He>> stalks away.
	<<else>>
		<<He>> stalks away.
	<</if>><<npcincr Avery lust 5>><<glust>>
	<br><br>
	<<endcombat>>
	<<avery_mansion_end_links>>
<<else>> /* Maxed pain */
	You crumple to the floor as you are overcome with pain. Avery watches with an impassable expression. <<He>> rubs at the knuckles of one hand as <<he>> says,
	<<if $enemyhealth gte $enemyhealthmax>>
		"Glad to see that you know how to take your punishment. But ideally you don't anger me in the first place. I expect you to follow through on your promises going forward. Understood?"<<npcincr Avery rage -1>><<larage>>
	<<else>>
		"It wouldn't have been as bad if you hadn't tried to fight back, <<= C.npc.Avery.rage gte 60 ? "<<girl>>" : "<<pcpetname "Avery">>">>. Remember that next time."<<npcincr Avery rage 1>><<garage>>
	<</if>><<npcincr Avery dom 1>><<gdom>>
	<br><br>
	With that, <<he>>
	<<if $avery_mansion?.schedule is "dinner">>
		leaves in the direction of the dining room.
	<<else>>
		walks away.
	<</if>>
	<br><br>
	<<endcombat>>
	<<avery_mansion_end_links>>
<</if>>
